Opgave 3

Find the driving point impedance seen by the voltage source in Figure P11â3 and the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s) / V_1(s).

Driving point impedans:

Dette er simpelt - hvad er \(V_1(s)\) ?

\[ V_1(s)= V_L + V_R + V_C \]

Omskrevet:

\[ V_1(s)= I(s)\left( L s + R + \frac{1}{Cs}\right) \]

Dermed:

\[ \frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)}= L s + R + \frac{1}{Cs} \]

Omskrevet:

\[ Z(s)=\frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)}= \frac{LCs^2 + RCs +1}{Cs} \]

Transfer function:

Da det er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler gÃ¦lder flg.:

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R}{Ls + \frac{1}{Cs}+R} \]

Omskrevet:

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R}{\frac{LCs^2 + RCs +1}{Cs}} \]

\[ \boxed{ T_V(s)=\frac{RCs}{LCs^2 + RCs +1} } \]

Opgave 7

Find the driving point impedance seen by the voltage source in Figure P11â7 and the voltage transfer function. T_V(s) = V_2(s)/V_1(s).

Driving point impedans

Da det er en operationsforstÃ¦rker, antages det at denne er idÃ©el og dermed er \(\boxed{Z_{in} =\infty}\).

Transfer function.

Det er en non-inverterende opstilling - derfor gÃ¦lder flg.:

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \] Hvor: \[ Z_1 = 2R \quad Z_2 = 2R||C \] \[ Z_2 = \frac{2R \cdot \frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}} \] Derfor: \[ T_V(s)=\frac{2R+\frac{2R\frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}}}{\frac{2R\frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}}} \]

Omskrevet: \[ \boxed{ T_V(s)=2RCs+2 } \]

Opgave 9

Find the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s)/V_1(s) in Figure P11â9.

Transfer function

Dette er to spÃ¦ndingsdelere i serie:

Deler 1: \[ H_1(s) = \frac{R}{L+R} \]

Deler 2 \[ H_2(s) = \frac{\frac{1}{Cs}}{\frac{1}{Cs}+R} \]

Dermed kan \(T_V(s)\) findes ved \[ T_V(s)= H_1(s)\cdot H_2(s) \] AltsÃ¥ \[ T_V(s) = \frac{R}{Ls+R} \cdot \frac{\frac{1}{Cs}}{\frac{1}{Cs}+R} \]

\[ \boxed{ T_V(s) = \frac{R}{CLRs^2+(CR^2+L)s+R} } \]

Opgave 15

Find the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s)/V_1(s) of the cascade connection in Figure P11â15. Locate the poles and zeros of the transfer function

Transfer function

KomponentID:

\(C_1 = 0.047 \mu F \;\) \(C_2 = 0.1 \mu F \;\)

\(R_1 = 22k\Omega\;\) \(R_2 = 1k\Omega \;\) \(R_3 = 10k\Omega \;\)

Venstresiden

Denne del af kredslÃ¸bet er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler bestÃ¥ende af \(C_1\) og \(R_1\)

\[ v_1(t) = \frac{R_1}{R_1+C_1} \]

Laplacetransformationen giver: \[ T_{Vdivider}(s) = \frac{R_1}{R_1+\frac{1}{C_1s}} \]

HÃ¸jresiden

OperationsforstÃ¦rkeren er koblet som en ikke inverterende forstÃ¦rker. Derfor: \[ T_{Vopamp}(s) = \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \]

Hvor: \[ Z_1 = R_3 \quad Z_2 = \frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2 \]

Dermed:

\[ T_{Vopamp}(s)=\frac{R_3+\frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2}{\frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2} \]

Med de rigtige vÃ¦rdier indsat:

\[ T_{Vdivider}(s)= \frac{22k\Omega}{22k\Omega+\frac{1}{0.047\mu F s}} = \frac{s}{s+967.1} \\ T_{Vopamp}(s)=\frac{10k\Omega+\frac{1}{0.1 \mu F s}+1k\Omega }{\frac{1}{0.1 \mu F s}+1k\Omega } = \frac{11(s+909.1)}{s+10000} \]

Hvorfor:

\[ T_V(s) = T_{Vdivider}(s) \cdot T_{Vopamp}(s) \]

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{C_1 R_1 s \cdot(C_2(R_2+R_2)s+1)}{(C_2R_2s+1)(C_1R_1s+1)} \]

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{s}{s+967.1} \cdot \frac{11(s+909.1)}{s+10000} \]

\[ \boxed{ T_V(s) = \frac{11s(s+909.1)}{(s+967.1)(s+10000)} } \] Det ses at funktionen har Ã©t nulpunkt: \(Z_1 = -909.1 \; rad/s\)

Desuden er der to poler: \(p_1 = -967.1\; rad/s \quad p_2 = -10000\; rad/s\)

Opgave 17

Find the impulse response at v_2(t) in Figure P11â17. Find the circuitâs step response.

Transfer function

Da det er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler gÃ¸r flg. sig gÃ¦ldende - efter en laplacetransformation:

\[V_2(s) = V_1(s)\;\cdot\; \frac{R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}}{R_1+R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}}\]

Omskrevet1: \[\underset{Y(s)}{\underbrace{V_2(s)}} = \underset{X(s)}{\underbrace{V_1(s)}}\;\cdot\; \underset{T_V(s) \; \lor \; H(s)}{\underbrace{\frac{R_2Cs+1}{R_1Cs+R_2Cs+1}}} \]

Transfer function

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R_2Cs+1}{R_1Cs+R_2Cs+1} \]

KomponentID:

\[ R_1 = 33k\Omega\\ R_2 = 47k\Omega\\ C = 0.15 \mu F \]

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{47k\Omega \cdot 0.15 \mu F \cdot s+1}{33k\Omega \cdot0.15 \mu F s+47k\Omega \cdot 0.15 \mu F s+1} = \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s+83.33} \] Her ses det at et enkelt nulpunkt er at finde \(z_1 = -141.8 \; rad/s\) og en enkelt pol \(p_1 = -83.33 \; rad/s\)

Impulserespons

Ved at gÃ¸re fÃ¸lgende: \[ v_{impulse}(t)= \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ T_V(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s+83.33} \right\} \] Dette giver: \[ \boxed{ v_{impulse}(t) = 0.5785 \cdot \left(\delta(t)+58.47e^{-83.33t}\right)\cdot u(t) }\]

Steprespons

Ved at gÃ¸re fÃ¸lgende:

\[ v_{step}(t)=\mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{1}{s} \cdot H(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{1}{s} \cdot T_V(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s^2+83.33s} \right\} \]

Dette giver:

\[ \boxed{ v_{step}(t) = (0.5875\cdot(1.702-0.702e^{-83.33t}))\cdot u(t) } \]

Driving point impedans

Vi har fÃ¸lgende KVL loop:

\[ v_1(t)=v_r+v_r+v_c \] Dette laplace transformeres:

\[ \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_1(t) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_{R1}(t) \right\} + \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_{R2}(t) \right\} + \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_C(t) \right\} \]

og giver: \[ V_1(s) = V_{R1}(s)+V_{R2}(s)+V_C(s) \]

En let omskrivning

\[ V_1(s)= I(s)(R_1+R_2)+ \frac{1}{Cs} I(s) \]

Dermed:

\[ \frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)} = R_1+R_2 + \frac{1}{Cs} \]

og vi har driving point impedansen:

\[ Z(s) = \frac{CR_1s+CR_2s+1}{Cs} \]

og vi har driving point impedansen / med vÃ¦rdier!: \[ \boxed{ Z(s) = \frac{80000\cdot(s+83.33)}{s} } \]

Opgave 35

The circuit in Figure P11â35 is in the steady state with v_1(t) = 10 cos 500t V. Find v_2SS(t).
Repeat for v_1(t) = 10 cos 1 kt V, and for v1(t) = 10 cos 10 kt V .
Where is the pole located?

KomponentID:

\[ R_1 = 1k\Omega\\ R_2 = 2k\Omega\\ C = 0.5 \mu F \]

Transfer function

Da det er en inverterende opsÃ¦tning gÃ¦lder flg.

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{-Z_2}{Z_1} \]

Hvor \[ Z_1 = R_1 \quad Z_2 = \frac{R_2 \cdot \frac{1}{Cs}}{R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}} \]

Derfor:

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{-\left( \frac{R_2 \cdot \frac{1}{Cs}}{R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}} \right)}{R_1} \] MedfÃ¸rer: \[ T_V(s)= \frac{-R_2}{R_1(R_2Cs+1)} \]

Med vÃ¦rdierne indsat:

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{-2000}{s+1000} \]

Denne funktion har Ã©n pol: \(p_1 = -1000\; rad/s\)

Impulse response

For at finde impulsresponenet:

\[ v_{impulse}(t)= \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ T_V(s) \right\} =v_{impulse}(t)= \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{-2000}{s+1000} \right\} \]

Dette medfÃ¸rer: \[ v_{impulse}(t)= -2000 e^{-1000t} u(t) \]
